cs.RO, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on controlling mobile robots using runtime verification techniques, which falls under the domain of robotics.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the development of a layered control architecture and the use of formal specifications, which are common topics in software engineering.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses temporal logic and regular expressions to describe safety requirements and mission specifications, which are topics related to logic in computer science.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses formal specifications to control robots in a reactive manner, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the control of mobile robots using runtime verification techniques, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
